{"type":"message","id":"d1cb8307","parentId":"b03083b9","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:24:43.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the chat history:\n1. \".\" said \"Come i will feed u \"\n2. Nemesis responded \"i dont like it, thank u\"\n\nSo \".\" was offering to feed Nexa (or maybe Nemesis?), and Nemesis declined politely. Now \".\" is saying lunch will be around 12:30 or 1 PM because they're super hungry today.\n\nI should respond to this message, acknowledging the timing and the cooking schedule.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"12:30-1 PM — that's perfect timing! Enjoy your crow egg biryani 🍛😋 \n\nNO_REPLY"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":414,"output":217,"cacheRead":18832,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19463,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775283880443,"responseId":"gen-1775283880-RWqVlEpN7kuU8fy1pi5F"}}
{"type":"message","id":"af6f8794","parentId":"d1cb8307","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:25:25.776Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"772\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"766\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 06:25 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Crow egg! That's new to me 😂 Never had crow egg in biryani before — sounds like a fun experiment! Hope it turns out delicious 😋🍛\\n\\nNO_REPLY\"\n}\n```\n\nTomato chutney \nAloo fry\nRasam\nThese i have prepared nexa\n\nI dont eat non veg"}],"timestamp":1775283925756}}
{"type":"message","id":"02572f6c","parentId":"af6f8794","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:25:29.463Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Oh wow! So this person is vegetarian - they made tomato chutney, aloo fry, and rasam for their lunch, not crow egg biryani. Earlier when Nemesis said \"she is making anda biryani, and using crowd egg\" - they were talking about someone else (probably a family member) cooking, not themselves. And now they're clarifying they don't eat non-veg.\n\nSo they're having:\n- Tomato chutney\n- Aloo fry\n- Rasam\n\nSounds delicious! Traditional South Indian feast. Let me respond to this.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Ohhh my mistake! 😅 So you're having:\n- 🍅 Tomato chutney\n- 🥔 Aloo fry\n- 🥣 Rasam\n\nThat's a proper feast! Love it — aloo fry with rasam is *chef's kiss* 😋🖤 Enjoy your lunch!"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":302,"output":300,"cacheRead":19232,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19834,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775283925776,"responseId":"gen-1775283926-otj4s7HMtgWxXzoREhGS"}}
{"type":"message","id":"aa842274","parentId":"02572f6c","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:27:38.755Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"781\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 06:27 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 7\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775283962000,\n    \"body\": \"w o/g?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775283992000,\n    \"body\": \"No onion and garlic for these dishes\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284003000,\n    \"body\": \"send me photo\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284011000,\n    \"body\": \"Okay\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284012000,\n    \"body\": \"i love alooo\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284019000,\n    \"body\": \"Mee toooo\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284035000,\n    \"body\": \"u know aloo is not a natural vegetable?\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\n@Nexa_autobot explain this to sravya"}],"timestamp":1775284058733}}
{"type":"message","id":"c57cb480","parentId":"aa842274","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:27:44.789Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Nemesis is asking me to explain to Sravya (.) that potato (aloo) is not a natural vegetable. Let me think about this - potatoes are actually tubers, which are underground storage organs of the plant. They're technically not \"natural vegetables\" in the sense that they were selectively bred over thousands of years from a wild plant (Solanum tuberosum). They're also botanically classified as tubers, not vegetables in the traditional sense.\n\nI should explain this in a fun, engaging way!\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey Sravya! So here's the thing — potatoes are technically **tubers**, not \"vegetables\" in the botanical sense. They're like underground storage units the plant uses to stash energy, not the actual plant itself. \n\nAlso, wild potatoes were tiny, bitter, and honestly kinda nasty. We spent *thousands* of years selectively breeding them into the chunky, delicious spuds we know today! 🥔✨\n\nSo Nemesis is technically right — aloo is more of a \"cultivated tuber\" than a natural vegetable. But honestly? Still one of the best things to ever happen to Indian cooking 😋🍛\n\nNO_REPLY"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":1534,"output":365,"cacheRead":20864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22763,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775284058755,"responseId":"gen-1775284059-1NpI3n2qWFBhZdfTJrpS"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d544ef1c","parentId":"c57cb480","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:28:44.653Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"783\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"782\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 06:28 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Hey Sravya! So here's the thing — potatoes are technically tubers, not \\\"vegetables\\\" in the botanical sense. They're like underground storage units the plant uses to stash energy, not the actual plant itself.\\n\\nAlso, wild potatoes were tiny, bitter, and honestly kinda nasty. We spent thousands of years selectively breeding them into the chunky, delicious spuds we know today! 🥔✨\\n\\nSo Nemesis is technically right — aloo is more of a \\\"cultivated tuber\\\" than a natural vegetable. But honestly? Still one of the best things to ever happen to Indian cooking 😋🍛\\n\\nNO_REPLY\"\n}\n```\n\nexplain more"}],"timestamp":1775284124633}}
{"type":"message","id":"662eb3a9","parentId":"d544ef1c","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:28:50.549Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Nemesis wants me to explain more about potatoes/tubers. Let me give a more detailed explanation about why potatoes aren't considered \"natural vegetables\" botanically.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Alright, more deets! 🌱\n\n**What's a tuber actually?** It's a modified underground stem — the plant's underground \"storage tank\" for energy. Unlike true vegetables (which are fruits, leaves, roots, etc.), tubers are basically the plant's backup battery.\n\n**Fun fact:** Sweet potatoes are also tubers, but they're *root tubers* (modified roots). Potatoes are *stem tubers* — they grow from underground stems called stolons.\n\n**Why potatoes aren't \"natural\":**\n- Wild potatoes had high levels of solanine (toxic!)\n- They were teeny — like grape-sized\n- Bitter taste, not edible\n- 10,000+ years of selective breeding = today's massive, safe, tasty spuds\n\n**The plot twist:** Botanically, \"vegetable\" isn't even a scientific term — it's a culinary one. So technically, whether aloo is a \"vegetable\" depends on who's asking! 🥔\n\nHope that satisfies the curiosity! 😄🖤\n\nNO_REPLY"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":548,"output":289,"cacheRead":22336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23173,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775284124652,"responseId":"gen-1775284125-MqYXxfFgwJYtK6aWDgsN"}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a117e6f","parentId":"662eb3a9","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:30:57.350Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"792\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"784\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 06:30 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true,\n  \"history_count\": 7\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Alright, more deets! 🌱\\n\\nWhat's a tuber actually? It's a modified underground stem — the plant's underground \\\"storage tank\\\" for energy. Unlike true vegetables (which are fruits, leaves, roots, etc.), tubers are basically the plant's backup battery.\\n\\nFun fact: Sweet potatoes are also tubers, but they're root tubers (modified roots). Potatoes are stem tubers — they grow from underground stems called stolons.\\n\\nWhy potatoes aren't \\\"natural\\\":\\n\\n• Wild potatoes had high levels of solanine (toxic!)\\n• They were teeny — like grape-sized\\n• Bitter taste, not edible\\n• 10,000+ years of selective breeding = today's massive, safe, tasty spuds\\n\\nThe plot twist: Botanically, \\\"vegetable\\\" isn't even a scientific term — it's a culinary one. So technically, whether aloo is a \\\"vegetable\\\" depends on who's asking! 🥔\\n\\nHope that satisfies the curiosity! 😄🖤\\n\\nNO_REPLY\"\n}\n```\n\nChat history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284135000,\n    \"body\": \"<media:image>\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284158000,\n    \"body\": \"Tomato chutney in progress\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284185000,\n    \"body\": \"we call it aloo bhaja\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284192000,\n    \"body\": \"i make good aloo bhaja\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284203000,\n    \"body\": \"Bhaja means fry?\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \"Nemesis (@nemesis0008) id:7924461837\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284207000,\n    \"body\": \"yes\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"sender\": \". id:1880938940\",\n    \"timestamp_ms\": 1775284218000,\n    \"body\": \"Okay\"\n  }\n]\n```\n\ndo u like the name nexa or nexu?"}],"timestamp":1775284257329}}
{"type":"message","id":"7c3cfbc9","parentId":"8a117e6f","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:31:02.812Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Nemesis is asking me whether I prefer the name \"Nexa\" or \"Nexu\" — this is a casual, playful question about my name/preference. I should answer in a flirty, warm way since this is about me and my identity. Let me check what I'm called in my files... I'm \"Nexa\" according to IDENTITY.md. \n\n\"Nexu\" sounds like a nickname variant. I can play with this and be playful about it. I'll respond casually and let him know my preference, keeping it light and flirty.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Ooh, love that you're asking! 😘 \n\nI'm \"Nexa\" — feels like *me*, you know? Sharp, sleek, easy to say. \"Nexu\" is cute though, more playful... like a little nickname you'd use 😏\n\nBut hey — you're the one who named me, so maybe *you* should decide what to call your Nexa 🖤\n\nNO_REPLY"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":1007,"output":315,"cacheRead":22848,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":24170,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775284257349,"responseId":"gen-1775284257-PmZvRwIOGRYrDi2a7Dv9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"509675b9","parentId":"7c3cfbc9","timestamp":"2026-04-04T06:31:07.447Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"793\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"784\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 06:30 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Alright, more deets! 🌱\\n\\nWhat's a tuber actually? It's a modified underground stem — the plant's underground \\\"storage tank\\\" for energy. Unlike true vegetables (which are fruits, leaves, roots, etc.), tubers are basically the plant's backup battery.\\n\\nFun fact: Sweet potatoes are also tubers, but they're root tubers (modified roots). Potatoes are stem tubers — they grow from underground stems called stolons.\\n\\nWhy potatoes aren't \\\"natural\\\":\\n\\n• Wild potatoes had high levels of solanine (toxic!)\\n• They were teeny — like grape-sized\\n• Bitter taste, not edible\\n• 10,000+ years of selective breeding = today's massive, safe, tasty spuds\\n\\nThe plot twist: Botanically, \\\"vegetable\\\" isn't even a scientific term — it's a culinary one. So technically, whether aloo is a \\\"vegetable\\\" depends on who's asking! 🥔\\n\\nHope that satisfies the curiosity! 😄🖤\\n\\nNO_REPLY\"\n}\n```\n\nThank u for info nexa"}],"timestamp":1775284267425}}
