{"type":"message","id":"84661ca7","parentId":"449fb1e3","timestamp":"2026-04-04T08:37:45.846Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sravya's asking about L1, L2, L3, L4 engineers - these are typically support/tier levels in IT support. Let me explain!\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Sure! Here's the breakdown 👇\n\n**🛠️ L1 — First Line Support**\n- Basic issues — password resets,How to use software, account lockouts\n- Usually fresh grads or junior support\n- Follows set scripts/kb articles\n- Resolves ~60-70% of issues\n\n**🛠️ L2 — Second Line Support**\n- More technical — software bugs, network issues, configuration problems\n- Deeper troubleshooting than L1\n- Usually 1-3 years experience\n- Handles ~20-30% of issues\n\n**🛠️ L3 — Third Line Support**\n- Complex issues — hardware failures, deep code bugs, infrastructure problems\n- Experts in their domain\n- 3-5+ years experience\n- Handles the tough 5-10% escalations\n\n**🛠️ L4 — Fourth Line Support**\n- Developer/engineering level — fix root cause, build patches, architectural changes\n- Often vendors or R&D teams\n- The last tier before it's \"won't fix\" or new development\n\nIn short: L1 = \"Did you try turning it off and on?\" → L4 = \"Let me rewrite the core code\" 🔧\n\nNO_REPLY"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":62803,"output":322,"cacheRead":96,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":63221,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775291856533,"responseId":"gen-1775291857-q6DM2VoN4zAwBcDanh4W"}}
{"type":"message","id":"b9a53cba","parentId":"84661ca7","timestamp":"2026-04-04T08:38:45.644Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"869\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"868\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \".\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Sat 2026-04-04 08:38 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \". (1880938940)\",\n  \"id\": \"1880938940\",\n  \"name\": \".\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Sure! Here's the breakdown 👇\\n\\n🛠️ L1 — First Line Support\\n\\n• Basic issues — password resets,How to use software, account lockouts\\n• Usually fresh grads or junior support\\n• Follows set scripts/kb articles\\n• Resolves ~60-70% of issues\\n\\n🛠️ L2 — Second Line Support\\n\\n• More technical — software bugs, network issues, configuration problems\\n• Deeper troubleshooting than L1\\n• Usually 1-3 years experience\\n• Handles ~20-30% of issues\\n\\n🛠️ L3 — Third Line Support\\n\\n• Complex issues — hardware failures, deep code bugs, infrastructure problems\\n• Experts in their domain\\n• 3-5+ years experience\\n• Handles the tough 5-10% escalations\\n\\n🛠️ L4 — Fourth Line Support\\n\\n• Developer/engineering level — fix root cause, build patches, architectural changes\\n• Often vendors or R&D teams\\n• The last tier before it's \\\"won't fix\\\" or new development\\n\\nIn short: L1 = \\\"Did you try turning it off and on?\\\" → L4 = \\\"Let me rewrite the core code\\\" 🔧\\n\\nNO_REPLY\"\n}\n```\n\nThanks for the info nexy\n\nBut y are u still usng NO_REPLY again?"}],"timestamp":1775291925556}}
