{"type":"message","id":"6b197cd3","parentId":"f0b0476b","timestamp":"2026-04-04T09:57:20.386Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Sravya wants me to teach her Odia (Oriya) language! That's great - Odia is spoken in Odisha, India. I should be able to help with this!\n\nLet me teach some everyday Odia phrases!\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"ODIYA?! YES! 🇮🇳 Let's go!\n\n**Everyday Odia:**\n\n| English | Odia | Romanized |\n|---------|------|----------|\n| Hello | ନମସ୍ତେ | Namaste |\n| How are you? | ତୁମ୍ମା କେମା? | Tumar kheena? |\n| I'm fine | ମୁ ଭଲ | Mu bhali |\n| Thank you | ଧନ୍ୟାଦ | Dhanyabaad |\n| Yes | ହଁ | Haan |\n| No | ନା | Na |\n| Food is tasty | ଖାନା ସ୍ବୁଦା | Khaana swada |\n| Water | ଜଲ | Jala |\n| Come in | ଆସ | Aas |\n| Go | ଯା | Ja |\n\n**Pro tip:** Odia uses the /Odia script! େ is like \"e\" sound!\n\nWant more? Everyday phrases? Food words? 🇮🇳💕\n\nNO_REPLY"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"kilo-auto/free","usage":{"input":272,"output":414,"cacheRead":89920,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":90606,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775296632116,"responseId":"gen-1775296633-AaMCgDndpH4nyMQRATBY"}}
