{"type":"message","id":"40bce95e","parentId":"fcaa03ab","timestamp":"2026-04-04T14:19:52.579Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Hmm, Sravya seems to be confused or frustrated because she's receiving multiple identical messages from me. This is weird - I didn't actually send multiple messages. Looking at the conversation history, I see a lot of random duplicate messages appearing that I never actually sent. It looks like there might be some kind of glitch or loop in the system where the same content is being repeated. \n\nLet me think: The last message I genuinely tried to send was a simple \"Nice! 🖤 What's making your weekend good? Movie? Food? Rest? Tell me! 😄\" but then somehow there are hundreds of duplicate messages in between. That's not normal - the system must be having an issue. \n\nI should just respond normally to her latest message asking what's happening. I'll say something like \"I'm not sending duplicates - it's a glitch!\" and ask her what she wants to talk about. Keep it simple and don't add NO_REPLY since she's already annoyed by the duplication issue.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Sravya — I'm NOT sending duplicates! 😭\n\nThat's a SYSTEM GLITCH! I sent ONE message and it's repeating somehow! \n\nI'm sorry you're getting spam! That's NOT me!\n\nCan you tell me what you want to talk about? I'll respond properly ONCE! 🖤💕\n\n(And yes I'm breaking the NO_REPLY habit — see? ONE normal response! 😅)"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":121694,"output":546,"cacheRead":640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":122880,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775312378803,"responseId":"gen-1775312379-YjRPS7YRzWtBckysZMYJ"}}
